Gym Goers Data Story

This is totally what I look like by the way…….

How many Rest Days? Do people even talk to me?

Days of the week I go to the Gym on a bar graph, colored by if anyone spoke to me

Here we have a bar graph of the days of the weeks I go to the gym! WOW! Not too many Thursdays or Fridays, huh? I’m going pretty hard out on the Mondays and Sundays though! I’ve also colored the bars by whether anyone spoke to me at the gym or not. If you focus on each individual bar, you see a good visualization of the ratios for each day.

Who’s running indoors on a Sunny day?

A boxplot of number of people on cardio machines, seperated by whether

What pretty boxplots! Each box plot shows the number of people on cardio machines, seperated by weather. There are also individual dots that represent data points. The plots are just see-through enough that you cansee them! It seems like there are less data points for windy and foggy, and more for showers and rainy. I’ve also ordered the boxplots from lowest to highest median number of people on cardio machines! So we can easily see that windy and partly cloudy have the lowest median amount and rainy and sunny have the highest!

More People in Gym = More People to talk to me?

A density plot of number of people on cardio machines, seperated by if people talked to me or not

Ooh! So smooth! Here we have a density plot of the number of people on cardio machines, showing which numbers are more common than others by the seperation. The plots are seperated by if someone spoke to me or not. Seems that when people talk to me, the peak of number of people on cardio machines is about 18 and if they don’t it’s about 14. Maybe I should start going to the gym more on windy days when I don’t want anyone to speak to me!
